### Problem04

Suppose that you start with an empty stack and interpret a letter to mean push and '–' to mean pop. Select all the choices below that leave 'e' at the bottom of the stack.

For instance : "a – b" means that we first push 'a' into an empty stack, and then pop 'a', and then push 'b'.

**Choices:**

A. a – b c – – d – e f g – h

B. a – b c – d – e – f g – h

C. a – b – c – d – e f g – h

D. a b c d – – – – e f g – h

E. a – b c – – d – e f g h –
choices: A. a – b c – – d – e f g – h
B. a – b c – d – e – f g – h
C. a – b – c – d – e f g – h
D. a b c d – – – – e f g – h
E. a – b c – – d – e f g h –
